ðŸ”¹ CRM Olympus HTTPS â€“ Autosys Jobs Deployment Update

We are deploying the CRM Olympus HTTPS Autosys jobs using a controlled two-step approach.

First, the job metadata is registered in OneRec ORAAS because direct deployment through CRM Autosys was failing with exit code 13 due to enterprise job launcher restrictions. Although ORAAS and CRM Autosys run on the same DA5, QA5, and PA5 instances, governance standards require job definitions to be registered in the ORAAS tables (OM_JOB_MASTER_INSTANCE and OM_JOB_PROPERTIES).

Once ORAAS registration is completed, we deploy the corresponding JIL files through the CRM Autosys repository. The JIL invokes the enterprise job launcher, ensuring secure and compliant execution.

